  "interpretation": "Camera and geometry align. The filament front is the exact col attribute and its back is Blender's achromatic max-RGB value branch. The browser now derives Generated coordinates from the filament material group's bounds, evaluates a clean-room lookup3/Perlin fBm Z wave, and applies forward-derivative bump normals. Relative to exact colors without bump, macro luminance MAE improves from 0.0628 to 0.0470, macro correlation from 0.808 to 0.939, and mean luminance delta from +0.0273 to +0.0083. Pixel MAE rises from 0.0644 to 0.0741 because the subpixel line pattern remains phase and raster-filter sensitive; high-frequency shader parity is not yet exact. The generic flat.w Background contract is implemented."
